bib.title: Detailed study of the intermediate structure in the Np-237 fission cross-section. Determination of the fission barrier parameters

free_txt: Thesis at Univ.Paris-Sud, Orsay.
This work constitutes a follow-up
to the measurement of Np-237 total and fission
cross-section performed at Saclay by D.Paya and
described in his thesis to Univ. Paris-Sud, Orsay.
See last reference below.
In accordance with Paya's instruction his fission
cross-section is superseded by present work.
Only fission cross-section has been measured by the
author who,however, uses the Paya total cross-sect.
in the analysis of his data and for deducting the
resonance parameters.
In the present work the energy range has also been
broadened to about 35 keV.

thesis at Univ.
Paris-Sud,Orsay.  The fission cross-section measured
in the present work has been normalized to the Paya
measurement by reproducing the areas of 30.39 and
41.33 eV resonances. The Paya data have been in turn
normalized to U-235 fission cross-section.
After careful chemical analysis of U-Np sample
used by Paya in his measurement,however, it was
realized that the U-235 content was 0.5+-0.05%
instead of the supposed 0.8%.
A further re-normalization has therefore been
performed by multiplying all results by 5/8.
